  <li><strong>DOCG vs DOC: Quality Hierarchy Determines Your Investment</strong> - Prosecco di Conegliano e Valdobbiadene DOCG represents the apex tier, sourced from steep hillside vineyards where hand-harvesting is mandatory and yields are strictly limited to 13.5 tons per hectare. These wines command 3-4x the price of DOC Prosecco delle Venezie but deliver superior complexity, minerality, and aging potential. Mid-tier Prosecco DOC Treviso offers excellent value with more character than basic DOC, while IGT Veneto versions provide everyday drinking options. Your budget determines the tier, but understanding these distinctions prevents overpaying or undervaluing.</li>

