    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Prosecco DOCG and DOC quality levels?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">DOCG Proseccos (Conegliano Valdobbiadene and Asolo) represent the highest quality tier, featuring hand-harvested grapes from steep hillside vineyards with superior soil drainage. DOC Proseccos come from the broader Veneto and Friuli regions with higher yields and machine harvesting. DOCG bottles typically cost $18-35 and offer more complexity, minerality, and aging potential compared to DOC versions at $8-18.</p>
