    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Which Prosecco alternatives offer similar quality at different price points?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">For similar freshness at lower cost, consider Spanish Cava from producers like Freixenet or Codorníu ($8-15), which offers more complexity through traditional method production. At higher price points, Franciacorta DOCG from Lombardy ($25-45) provides Prosecco's Italian heritage with Champagne-level sophistication, while Austrian Sekt from Wachau offers comparable minerality and elegance to premium Prosecco DOCG.</p>
