  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do single vineyard Proseccos compare to blended versions?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Single vineyard Proseccos like Cartizze from Valdobbiadene or specific "Rive" designations showcase unique terroir characteristics - Cartizze offers honeyed richness from calcareous soils, while steep-slope Rive bottlings display intense minerality. Blended Proseccos provide consistency and balanced flavor profiles year after year, making them ideal for regular consumption, while single vineyard expressions cost 50-100% more but reward wine enthusiasts seeking distinctive terroir expression.</p>
